hu.invitech.insight.processor.sdk.v1.api

Interface ServerInterface


  • public interface ServerInterface
    Provides a service for assigning/unassigning servers, and changing tokens of assigned servers.

    This service needs to be accessible at the following path: /v1 "/server"

    Version:
    1

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Status assignServer(ServerInfo serverInfo)
      Assigns a server to the processor with the given token.
      void changeToken(ChangeToken changeToken)
      Changes the token of an assigned server.
      void unassignServer(ServerInfo serverInfo)
      Unassigns a server from the processor with the given token.

    • Method Detail

      • assignServer

        Status assignServer(ServerInfo serverInfo)
        Assigns a server to the processor with the given token.

        Should be accessible at the following path: POST "/assign"

        HTTP status codes
        Code Text Description
        403 Forbidden The token is empty or invalid
        200 OK OK
        Parameters:
        serverInfo - the information about the server to be assigned (see ServerInfo)
        Returns:
        the current processor status related to this server (see Status)
        Since:
        version 1

      • unassignServer

        void unassignServer(ServerInfo serverInfo)
        Unassigns a server from the processor with the given token.

        Should be accessible at the following path: POST "/unassign"

        HTTP status codes
        Code Text Description
        403 Forbidden The token is empty, invalid, or assigned to a different server than the caller
        204 No Content OK
        Parameters:
        serverInfo - the information about the server to be unassigned (see ServerInfo)
        Since:
        version 1

      • changeToken

        void changeToken(ChangeToken changeToken)
        Changes the token of an assigned server.

        Should be accessible at the following path: POST "/token"

        HTTP status codes
        Code Text Description
        403 Forbidden The new token is empty, invalid, unassigned, or assigned to a different server than the caller
        400 Bad Request The old or the new token is missing or they are both the same
        204 No Content OK
        Parameters:
        changeToken - the information required for the token change (see ChangeToken)
        Since:
        version 1
